text: If you're going for zombie army, I'd lean into Varina personally, as White gives you a bunch of great options for established board presences, and Varina gives you fantastic card filtering and the way to make more zombies. That being said, Scarab God ain't broke, don't fix it.

Is everyone that is playing Witch's Cottage also playing Mortuary Mire? I've seen so many people excited about Cottage, but no one mentions Mire what so ever. I can't see myself running Cottage as there is a percentage of the time where it will enter tapped and I won't get the Reclaim effect from it. Id rather always have the effect 100% of the time and deal with a tapped land, since that's the reason why I am putting it in the deck.
what? mortuary mire is terrible in comparison

1. witch's cottage is a swamp:  you can fetch it at instant speed, it works with some of the mana doublers
2. in teh case where I'm putting witch's cottage down as a tapped land, I'm going to guess that I don't want to put a creature on the top of my library anyways. I want another land. Plus it's not often that I have a creature I care about in the bin before t3

I'm not super excited about the card, but it's still not terrible. Incremental improvement over a swamp
mortuary mire coming into play tapped always just makes it a no go for me

For my personal decks, I don’t think there’s many that care about the difference between the two. I have a lot of three color decks, and my landbases are pretty scattered across them all. I think Varina/Aminatou and Windgrace are the places I’d likely play it.

I do agree that the always-on effect of Mire is definitely a plus though for decks that don’t have as many fetches and want the effect.
